      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Publications</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Publications series contains newsletters, pamphlets, a Girls Friendly Society magazine published in 1888, and a manual for House Committee members from 1954-1960. The majority of the pamphlets are an annual series that was used to publicize the Holiday House from 1903 to 1950. There are also a number of pamphlets that outline the revisions made to the constitution and the by-laws of the Girls Friendly Society between 1904 and 1963.</p>
        </scopecontent>
